author: COMSOL
description: The circular motion of a cylindrical homogeneous copper rotor in the magnetic field from a stationary permanent magnet generates induced eddy currents in the rotor. The magnetic field penetration and eddy current distribution is limited by the velocity skin effect. The example is a general introduction to using the rotating machinery interface in 3D.
